{"questionId":"25505","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A survey at a swimming pool is given to one adult in each family. The age of the&nbsp;adult, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math> years old, and of their eldest child, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math> years old, are recorded.</p>\n<p>The ages of the eldest child are summarized in the following box and whisker diagram.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/f1b12086f78c59245f2e522bf19532385a544318.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The regression line of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math> on <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math> is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>7</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mi>c</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>20</mn></math>.&nbsp;The regression line of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math> on <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math> is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>One of the adults surveyed is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>42</mn></math> years old. Estimate the age of their eldest child.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>choosing&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>42</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>12</mn></math>&nbsp;(years old)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"25505","referenceCode":"22M.1.SL.TZ1.3b.i","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"One of the adults surveyed is 42 years old. Estimate the age of their eldest child.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.3—Mean, median, mode. Mean of grouped data, standard deviation. Quartiles, IQR","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.4—Pearsons, scatter diagrams, eqn of y on x","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.10—X on y regression line"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}